## Phase 3: Frontend Redesign (upgrade_2.txt)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Layout Suggestion for Result Page:** Keep the **Quick Action Header** (scores + tug-of-war + gaps + exposure) at the top spanning full width. Below it, place the **Executive Summary** (collapsible). Then replace the horizontal tabs with a **left vertical sidebar** (20% width) + **main content area** (80% width). The existing Dashboard charts (Risk Doughnut, Compliance Grid, Radar) can be **moved into their respective tabs** so they appear contextually when the user selects that category, rather than being separate. This makes the top area focused on strategic overview, and tabs become deep-dive panels.

#### [MODIFY] [ResultsPage.jsx](file:///c:/anujDrive/NLP_Project/frontend/src/pages/ResultsPage.jsx)
Complete restructure:
- Replace horizontal tabs with left vertical sidebar navigation
- Add severity badges and counts to sidebar items
- Each tab's content area gets the enhanced designs below
- Integrate What-If inline into clause cards (Edit & Re-Analyze button per clause)
- Remove What-If as a separate tab

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/anujDrive/NLP_Project/frontend/src/components/Dashboard.jsx)
Redesign into Quick Action Header:
- **A.** Safety Score — large circular gauge (derived from risk + compliance + ambiguity)
- **B.** Responsibility Tug-of-War bar (consultant % vs company %)
- **C.** Critical Gaps indicator (missing clauses count + high-severity risk count, clickable)
- **D.** Financial Exposure badge (total contract value + liability cap status)

#### [MODIFY] [ClauseCard.jsx](file:///c:/anujDrive/NLP_Project/frontend/src/components/ClauseCard.jsx)
- Add risk color strip on left border (red/yellow/green)
- Add severity label and impact icons
